OL,6,FThe report reads: "Aged debt becomes
OL,7,Fincreasingly difficult to collect for
OL,8,Fseveral reasons including: greater
OL,9,Flikelihood of there being a change in
OL,10,Fthe debtor's circumstances ` they may
OL,11,Fhave moved, become insolvent for
OL,12,Fexample; debtors may have other,
OL,13,Fhigher priority debts; debtors
OL,14,Fquestion the legitimacy of the debt."
OL,16,FOutstanding housing benefit
OL,17,Foverpayments totalled #18.6 million,
OL,18,Fwhile council tenant rent and related
OL,19,Fcharges such as those paid by
OL,20,Fleaseholders was #15.2 million,.
